Stuck with this for days ! Have tried all suggestions from previous forums.......importHelpers, clean up node. Without Ivy there are no issues. I get the below error on using Ivy Angular 10. I can not use postinstall :ngcc  to fix this since npm install is not run . Build files for the library are simply copied under node_modules ('@abc/uiplatform') after ng build is run for the library.

UIPlatformModule is a module within an internal package '@abc/uiplatform' which is built using ng build and then copied under node_modules under a folder structure "@abc/uiplatform".  

```
BUILD ERROR ../node_modules/@infogix/uiplatform/uiplatform.module.d.ts:2:22 - error NG6002: Appears in the NgModule.imports of ControlModule, but could not be resolved to an NgModule class.

This likely means that the library (@infogix/uiplatform) which declares UIPlatformModule has not been processed correctly by ngcc, or is not compatible with Angular Ivy. Check if a newer version of the library is available, and update if so. Also consider checking with the library's authors to see if the library is expected to be compatible with Ivy.

2 export declare class UIPlatformModule {
```

